SPRING tides are the ones where the sun and moon are on opposite sides of the earth (full and new moons) so the pull is strongest and the low tide is the lowest while the high is the highest. NEAP tides are when sun and moon are at sort of right angles to earth, so tides are less extreme. A coastal storm at spring tide can cause more damage than one at neap.

